<module>
    <h>bàta</h>
    <p><g>bàta</g>
        <en>a boat</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
            noun</a>.</p>

    <p>Examples of <g>bàta</g> as the subject of the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
        – <ul>
            <li>non-specified – <ul>
                    <li>with attributive adjective – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Bha bàta beag air an traigh.</gd>
                                <tr>There was a little boat on the beach.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>specified – <ul>
                    <li>unmodified – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Tha am bàta air a’ chladach.</gd>
                                <tr>The boat is on the shore.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 17</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <!--<p>Examples of <g>bàta</g> as the subject of other verbs – <ul>
            <li>indefinite –</li>
            <li>definite –</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>Examples of <g>bàta</g> as the object of a (transitive) verb – <ul>
            <li>indefinite –</li>
