    <p>Examples of <g>bàta</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=an^preposition"
                ><g>an</g></a>
        <en>in</en> – <ul>
            <!--<li>indefinite –</li>-->
            <li>specified – <g>anns a bhàta</g>
                <en>in the boat</en> – <ul>
                    <li>unmodified – <xl>
                            <!--<li>
                        <gd>Tha an duine anns a’ bhàta.</gd>
                        <tr>The man is in the boat.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 17</ref>
                    </li>-->
                            <li>
                                <gd>Cha robh duine anns a’ bhàta.</gd>
                                <tr>There was no one in the boat.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <module>
        <h>bàtaichean</h>
        <p><g>bàtaichean</g>
            <en>boats</en> is the plural form of <g>bàta</g>.</p>
        <p>Examples of <g>bàtaichean</g> as the object of a (transitive) <a href="?xx=verbs/verbs"
                >verb</a> – 
            <ul>
                <li>non-specified –
                <ul>
                    <li>unmodified – 
                        <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Bha mi aig a’ chladach an diugh. Chunnaic mi bàtaichean air a’ mhuir.</gd>
                                <tr>I was at the shore today. I saw boats on the sea.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </module>

</module>
